The paper deals with the analysis of channels and their capacity, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The use of LDPC codes suggests a focus on error correction and coding (cs.CC). The mention of input distribution and capacity-achieving distributions suggests a focus on network information theory (cs.NI) and source coding (cs.SI). Finally, the mention of Markov channels suggests a focus on stochastic processes and probability theory (cs.DS).
